// Modified codes generated by Free Claude
//
//  DeviceRunLengthEncode::Encode  →  std::unique_copy    (keys)       [GPU]
//                                 +  std::copy_if        (offsets)    [GPU]
//                                 +  std::adjacent_difference (lengths)[GPU]
//
// USM strategy
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//  • sycl::malloc_shared<T>(n, q)  — allocates memory accessible from both
//    host and device without explicit copy calls.
//  • A thin RAII wrapper (UsmVector<T>) is used throughout so that USM
//    pointers are freed correctly even if an exception is thrown.
//  • The execution policy is built from the same sycl::queue that owns the
//    USM allocations:  oneapi::dpl::execution::make_device_policy(q)
//    This guarantees that oneDPL submits kernels to the correct device and
//    that pointer provenance matches.
//  • Host-only work (Initialize, Solve, correctness checks) uses raw pointers
//    into the USM buffers directly — no extra copies needed.
// =============================================================================

